KATSINA – The dilapidated Sha’iskawa clinic in Mani local government area of Katsina state has been temporarily relocated to an Islamiyya school. When the Daily Independent reporter visited the area on Tuesday, it was observed that, the building housing the clinic is at the verge of collapse. Malam Musa Maizuwa Farusa, a resident in the area who confirmed the relocation of the clinic, said he personally provided a location to the clinic to enable their women, children and the aged to get attended to whenever they wanted. He also maintained that, the clinic which provides services to Sha’iskawa community and it’s environs only functions on Fridays. Similarly, the clinic at Filin Kwallo area of Jani Village in the same local government area is not fit for humans. The clinic is operating side by side with an abandoned ward that has been turned into a feaces ground. The smell from the the abandoned ward can be perceived from the clinic consultation room. -Advertisement- POLL Meanwhile, at Durbi Ta Kusheyi village, the MDG hospital built in 2009 has been abandoned and infested by bats. During our reporter’s visit to the hospital, there were no any health personnel and patronage by patients. All the beds, offices and laboratory at the health facility were completely abandoned and in a terrible stage. Dr. Shamsudeen Yahaya Kankia, the Executive Secretary, Katsina State Primary Health Care Development Agency, while responding to questions from newsmen said the state government has resolved to ensure that, at least one hospital is functional in each ward across the state.